title: Georgia Senate 2026 - Day 7 PM Session
summary:
Here is a summary of the Georgia Senate 2026 - Day 7 PM Session:

**Overview**:
The session included the introduction of several new bills, reports from Senate committees, and procedural matters. Notable was the suspension of a rule to allow assignment of a gubernatorial appointment to a committee.

**Key Actions**:
- **SB 411**: Bill to amend Title 43 related to professional services
- **SB 412**: Bill to amend education code related to Part 4 of Article 17 of Chapter 2 of Title 20
- **SB 605**: Bill introduced (first reading)
- **SR 605**: Resolution introduced (first reading)

**Bills Introduced (First Reading)**:
- SB 411-420, SR 584, SR 593

**Notable Moments**:
- Suspension of Senate Rule 3-3.1A to allow assignment of a gubernatorial appointment to the Judicial Qualifications Commission
- Morning devotion led by the Rules Committee Chairman

**Votes**:
None recorded.

**Attendance**:
The Senate granted unanimous consent to excuse several senators from the session.

**Adjournment**:
The transcript does not include the time of adjournment or the date of the next session.
